t depends strongly on the\nage of the stellar population for high-mass slope variations. The normalization\nof the [Mg/Fe]$-\\sigma_e$ relation is decreased (increased) for bottom-\n(top-)heavy IMF variations, while the slope is not strongly affected.\nBottom-heavy variations have little impact on galaxy metallicities, half-light\nradii of early-type galaxies, or star formation rates, while top-heavy\nvariations significantly increase these quantities for high-mass galaxies,\nleading to tension with observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Apr 2018 14:57:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 25 Jun 2018 11:57:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 6 Jul 2018 08:57:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-17"}
